\brief Function to enable or disable the DC Notch filter within the PDC unit depending on the input boolean disableNotchFilter This function makes usage of 4 SPI transactions when disabling the filter or 6 SPI transactions when enabling it. It supports PDC multicast \details This function can be used to disable the DC Notch filter, in this case the input dcNotchCoeff is not used. On the other hand, when enabling the DC Notch filter, the cutoff frequency is set too and therefore the input dcNotchCoeff is used. This function\ will internally call rfeHwPdc_dcNotchFilterCoeffSetter() to set the cutoff frequency, please read there how to set this parameter. \param [in] pdcIndex: PDC index to be mapped into its SPI module address counterpart \param [in] disableNotchFilter: boolean to disable ( true) the filter or not ( false) \param [in] dcNotchCoeff: cutoff frequency when enabling the filter, in case of disabling the filter this parameter will be ignored. \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER

\brief Function that sets the specified output sampling rate, Fsout, in the selected PDC profile for selected PDC unit This function makes usage of SPI transactions and supports PDC multicast \param [in] rxSelect: Selection of any combination of RX for corresponding PDC unit index where selected sampling rate is going to be applied to \param [in] pdcProfileIndex: PDC profile where the sampling rate is going to be applied to \param [in] pdcOutputSamplingRate: sampling rate to set \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER

\brief This function is intended to set the equalizers coeffs for the selected profile of the chosen PDC This function makes usage of SPI transactions and supports PDC multicast \param [in] pdcIndex : PDC unit index where the equalizer coeffs are going to be applied to \param [in] pdcProfileIndex: PDC profile where the equalizer coeffs are going to be applied to \param [in] eqCoeffs : structure containing the three coeffs for the equalizer \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER

\brief This function is intended to set the phase correction value for I and Q for the selected profile of the chosen PDC Notice that phase correction for I an Q should be defining using 12bits (11bits info + 1 bit sign), the function checks that the set value is not larger than a 12 bit number in case of being, it will throw an error and the setting of the correction in phase won't happen This function makes usage of SPI transactions and PDC multicast \param [in] pdcIndex : PDC unit index where the phase correction is going to be applied to \param [in] pdcProfileIndex: PDC profile where the phase correction is going to be applied to \param [in] pdcPhaseCorrectionParams: structure holding the correction values to be set for I, Q and adjacency \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER

\brief This function is intended to set the amplitude/phase correction value for I and Q in validation mode for the selected profile of the chosen PDC. This function makes usage of SPI transactions and supports PDC multicast \param [in] pdcIndex : PDC unit index where the phase correction is going to be applied to \param [in] pdcProfileIndex: PDC profile where the phase correction is going to be applied to \param [in] iqcAmpCorrection : value of the correction to apply for the amplitude \param [in] iqcPhaseCorrection: value of the correction to apply for the phase \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER

\brief This function is intended to enable or disable the spectrum shift of Fs/2 This function makes usage of SPI transactions \param [in] pdcIndex: PDC unit index where the Fs/2 shift is going to be applied to \param [in] enable: boolean indicating whether to apply the shift ( true) or not ( false) \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER

\brief This function is intended to deliver I, Q or IQ signals to the packer from the selected PDC. I component is the normal use case, whereas Q and IQ are intended more for validation and support PDC multicast This function makes usage of SPI transactions, setting I or IQ will require 6 SPI transactions, setting Q will require 8 SPI transactions since we need to address a second PDC \details In order to have a better view of how the PDC output can be selected check out sections 2.3.16 and 2.3.21.1 from STRX AS MBS PDC for ES1.docx \param [in] pdcIndex PDC unit index where selected sampling rate is going to be applied to \param [in] selectedOutput : output to be set for the PDC, I, Q or IQ \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER

\brief This function is intended to set the decimation filters band mode between steep ( default) or narrow This function make usage of SPI transactions \attention The given name of this function is ambiguous and confusing given that this function sets the decimation filer band mode, and not the decimation factor as it suggests by the name. This is keep like this for the time being to be aligned with the rfeCfg.h provided to the customer \param [in] rxSelect: Selection of any combination of RX for corresponding PDC unit index where the Fs/2 shift is going to be applied to \param [in] bandMode: decimation filter band mode or narrow or steep narrow mode \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER

\brief This function is intended to select whether bypassing or not all filters in selected PDC This function makes usage of SPI transitions and supports PDC multicast \param [in] pdcIndex: PDC unit index where the filters are going to be enabled/disabled \param [in] bypassFilters: variable (uint8_t) indicating which filters will be disabled on PDC via its bits. Consult description of rfeHwPdc_filterBypass_t type I.e. bypassFilters = 0x3 = 0b00000011 -> indicates that PDC ICQ (bit 0) and PDC DC Notch (bit 1) filters will be disabled \param [in] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER

\brief This function is intended to get the whole clipping register status of the PDC filters. The function allows also the reseting of clipping register if setting resetClippingFlag to true This function makes usage of SPI transactions and PDC multicast \details This function can be used in combination with the macro RFE_HW_PDC_COMMON_CLIPPED_BIT_GETTER() to extract only one of the flags if desired \param [in] pdcIndex: PDC unit index where the clipping register get is going to be applied to \param [in] clippingBitToRead: boolean to clean the content of the clipping register is set to true or keep as it is is set to false \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER \return [out] rfeHwSpi_register32_t register containing the all clipping flags for the PDC filters

\brief Function to set the PDC bit width (also called output rounding in documentation) This function makes usage of SPI transactions \param [in] rxSelect: Selection of any combination of RX for corresponding PDC unit index where the bitwidth is going to be applied to \param [in] bitWidth: PDC bitwidth to be set \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER

\brief Function to set the PDC Clipping count limit This function makes usage of SPI transactions \param [in] pdcIndex: PDC unit index where the Clipping Count is going to be applied to \param [in] pdcClippingCountLimit: PDC Clipping count limit \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER

\brief This function is intended to enable the correlator in the PDC. This function makes usage of SPI transactions \param [in] pdcIndex: PDC unit index where the correlator is going to be applied to \param [in] enableCorrelator: boolean to enable(true) or disable (false) the correlator \param [in] correlatorIntgTime: set the correlator samples ( integration time) to be used by the correlator \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER

\brief This function is intended to read the correlator output I & Q This function is using SPI transactions \param [in] pdcIndex: PDC unit index where the correlator is going to be applied to \param [in/out] pCorrelatorOutputI : result of the correlator for I component \param [in/out] pCorrelatorOutputQ : result of the correlator for Q component \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER

\brief This function is intended to read the selected PDC ADC Overload Counter This function is using SPI transactions \param [in] pdcIndex: PDC unit index where the ADC overload counter will be read from \param [in/out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER \return uint32_t containing the ADC counter value, notice that this value is using only using lower 22bits, so a clipping value will be represented as 2^(RFE_HW_PDC_PDC_ADC_OL_CNT_ADC_OL_COUNTS_LEN-1)

\brief Function to control the DFT MUXER output from the PDC This function makes usage of SPI transactions and supports PDC multicast \details This function can be better optimized for SPI transactions by rewriting it based on rfeHwPdc_outputSelector(). At this point was preferred to reuse the existing functionality to reuse the defines types. \param [in] pdcIndex: PDC unit index where the Fs/2 shift is going to be applied to \param [in] pdcProfileIndex: PDC profile where the phase correction is going to be applied to \param [in] selectedOutput: variable to control PDC output to be set I, Q or IQ \param [in] dfTSelectedOutput: variable to control the output of DFT muxer \param [in] pdcOutputSamplingRate: variable to control sampling rate of selected PDC \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER

\brief Function to set extra supported sampling rates for PDC for DfT/Validation This function makes usage of SPI transactions supports PDC multicast for sampling rates <= 80MHz, \details This function enables the usage of 160MHz sampling rate for the PDC's and 80MHz sampling rate using Decimator 12 filter, the other sampling frequencies are being configured by calling to the standard rfeHwPdc_samplingRateSetter() internally Further when looking for 1bit streaming mode use this function with input function rfeHwPdc_effectiveSamplingFrequency_160MHz_e since this is taking the ADC RAW Data to the output \param [in] pdcIndex: PDC unit index where the Fs/2 shift is going to be applied to \param [in] pdcProfileIndex: PDC profile where sampling rate is going to be applied to \param [in] pdcOutputSamplingRate: variable to control sampling rate of selected PDC \param [in] useDeci12Filter: boolean to control whether using filter deci12 (true) or standard deci11(false) for fs = 80MHz \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER

\brief Function intended to enable or disable PDC Equalizer. This function make use of SPI transactions and support PDC multicast address \param [in] pdcIndex: PDC unit index where EQ setting is going to be applied to \param [in] enable: variable to enable ( true ) or disable ( false ) the Equalizer \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER \return bool current status of the PDC Equalizer after calling this function

\brief Function intended to put Deci1 on hold \details Notice that register configured here used inverted logic \param [in] pdcIndex selected PDC where Deci1 will be set on hold or not based on selected sampling rate \param [in] enable boolean indicating whether enabling on hold Dec10 ( true, register content will be 0x0 ) or disabling hold on Dec10 ( false, register content will be 0x1 ) \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER

\brief This function is intended to enable the dicimator 12 on the selected PDC This function supports PDC Multicast \details Notice that in order to use the decimator 12 the Cordic filter and the Fshift3 filter are internally disabled by this function \param [in] pdcIndex selected PDC where the deci12 will be enabled (true) or disabled (false) \param [in] enable flag indicating whether to enable or not deci12 \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER

\brief This function sets the PDC I & Q swap at the input and output of all PDCs. \details The I & Q paths need to be swapped for negative chirps (falling chirp slope) to have the right side of the spectrum filtered by the Hilbert filter. Due to a HW issue (see STRX-3989), this swap is not automatically done. This function should be called by MainFsm to set the I-Q swap according to the direction of chirps in the upcoming chirp sequence. \pre NIL \param [in] iqSwapEnable - Enables/disables I-Q swap at input and ouput of PDC. \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER - Error handling parameter: On success rfe_error_none_e is returned \return NIL \post NIL \ingroup NIL

\brief Function intended to enable the use of PDC multicast address when writing SPI commands on those function that support it \details This function sets/disables the internal PDC global usePdcMulticastAddr which will indicate internally to PDC driver to make use the PDC Multicast in all PDC SPI writes when supported (only for spi rfeHwSpi_write calls). If the function is called to enable the multicast SPI address all PDC driver calls issued afterwards will be writing the register to all four PDCs. Once disabled, calls to PDC driver won't use the multicast SPI address. \param [in] enable: boolean indicating to use or not PDC Multicast address module in PDC SPI writes command \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER

\brief Function to map customer sampling rate to validation sampling rate \param[in] customerSamplingRate customer sampling rate to be mapped \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER error handling parameter. It will be non zero if an error occurs \return rfeHwPdc_dftSamplingFrequency_t validation sampling rate associated to the customer sampling rate

\brief Function dedicate to override ES1 defaults register map values for PHASE CORRECTION I/Q in all PDC profiles depending on selected output sampling rate(Fsout) This function makes usage of SPI transactions and supports PDC multicast \details This function will override ES1 default register map values for PHASE CORRECTION I/Q using these values. Also the function sets accordingly PDC Equalizer coefficients filter, needed to achieve the full PHASE Correction on I/Q tackling filter group delay. 1. For Steep narrow band mode fsOut / MHz | PDC_PHASE_COR_I | PDC_PHASE_COR_Q ------------ | ------------- |------------- 80 | 1650 | -1213 40 | 1816 | -947 20 | 2043 | 141 10 | 1868 | 840 2. For Narrow band mode fsOut / MHz | PDC_PHASE_COR_I | PDC_PHASE_COR_Q ------------ | ------------- |------------- 80 | 1647 | -1217 40 | 2028 | 283 20 | 1583 | 1299 10 | 1037 | 1766 3. Equalizer coefficients on equalizerCoefficients according to PDC design document Table 17 and TABle 18 combined fsOut / MHz | EQ_COEFF_1 | EQ_COEFF_2 | EQ_COEFF_3 | ------------ | -----------|-----------------|-------------| fsOut / MHz | k0xa1 | k0 or re(k0xa0) | imag(k0xa0) | ------------ | -----------|-----------------|-------------| 80 | 10890 | -5397 (k0) | 0 | 40 | 11335 | -5086 |-3695 | 20 | 11457 | -5283 |-3838 | 10 | 9122 | -1504 |-1093 | \param [in] profileIndex variable indicating the profile to be selected to apply phase correction and EQ coeffs values \param [in] outputSamplingRate sampling rate to be used since this determines the phase correction to use \param [in] filterMode to use since this determines the phase correction to use \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER - Error handling parameter: On success rfe_error_none_e is returned

\brief This function applies initial configuration to PDC (when LLDOPDC is transitioned from Power Off to Power On). \details This function applies initial configuration to PDC (when LLDOPDC is transitioned from Power Off to Power On). This function should be called during RFE Power Off to RFE Power On \pre \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER - Error handling parameter: On success #RFE_ERROR_IS_NO_ERROR is true, On failure #RFE_ERROR_IS_ERROR is true \return NIL \post NIL \ingroup NIL

This function doesn't make any SPI transaction \param [in] inPdcCtl3Reg: content of PDC_CTL3 register \param [in] disable : boolean to disable PDC output ( true) or not (false) \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER \return rfeHwSpi_register32 register modified to disable PDC output.

\brief Function that maps the pdcIndx for the Rx with its SPI module address so that the API may make use of this function This function doesn't make any SPI transaction \param [in] pdcIndex: PDC index to be mapped into its SPI module address counterpart \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER \return SPI module address counterpart (rfeHwSpi_module_t) for the PDC selected

\brief Function intended to choose the CTL0 SPI address based on the PDC profile index This function doesn't make usage of SPI transactions \param [in] pdcIndex PDC unit index where selected sampling rate is going to be applied to \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER \return SPI module address counterpart (rfeHwSpi_module_t) for the selected CTLO register

\brief This function sets the cutoff frequency for the DC Notch filter. This function makes usage of SPI transactions and supports PDC multicast address \details Refer to section 2.3.12 DC Notch Filter from STRX AS MBOS PDC for ES1.docx to have better understanding on how the cut off frequency is processed by the PDC DC Notch filter. According to the mentioned documentation, the register value to be set can be obtained via the expression \f$ dcNotchCoeff = round \Bigl( \bigl(1-cos(\frac{f_c}{f_s}*2\pi)+\sqrt{cos^2(\frac{f_c}{f_s}*2\pi)-4*cos(\frac{f_c}{f_s}*2\pi)+3} \bigr) *2^{16} *2 \Bigr) \f$ \param [in] pdcIndex: PDC index to be mapped into its SPI module address counterpart \param [in] dcNotchCoeff : register content indicating DC notch filter cutoff frequency, see details above. \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER

\brief Function to enable the Q component in the PDC output unit This function makes usage of SPI transactions and supports PDC multicast address \details This function will enable/disable Q component by setting RFE_HW_PDC_PDC_CTL4_IMAG_OUT_EN_BIT \param [in] pdcIndex PDC index to be mapped into its SPI module address counterpart \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER

\brief Function to return rxSelect value from pdcIndex \details This function returns rxSelect value based on value from pdcIndex \param [in] pdcIndex PDC index to be mapped into its SPI module address counterpart \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER \return rfeHwSpi_register32 register modified to disable PDC output.
